            <TextArea editable="false" layoutX="88.0" layoutY="80.0" prefHeight="520.0" prefWidth="657.0" text="Robots Types:&#10;Scout - 1 Attack, 1 Health, 3 Movement, 2 Range&#10;Sniper - 2 Attack, 2 Health, 2 Movement, 3 Range&#10;Tank - 3 Attack, 3 Health, 1 Movement, 1 Range&#10;&#10;Teams (2, 3, or 6):&#10;-Red, Orange, Yellow, Green, Blue, and Purple&#10;&#10;Game Flow:&#10;-With two players, red and green are used, and the board has 5 spaces on a side&#10;-With three players, red and yellow and blue are used, the board can have 5 or 7 spaces on a side&#10;-With six players, all colours are used and the board has 7 spaces on a side.&#10;-The colours are assigned randomly&#10;-All robots enter in their home space, facing along the arrow&#10;-Any number of robots, including ones from opposing teams, can occupy the same space&#10;-A turn begins with Red team playing its robot with greatest movement; then orange does the same....finally blue plays its greatest-movement robot - this completes one round&#10;-A second round is played where Red team plays their next highest moving robot, then orange, ... , then up to blue. &#10;-Thus, every robot gets on play per turn, fastest robots move first.&#10;-Note that Red's highest movement robot might not be&#10;-If a team does not have a robot to play during a round, skip to the next colour&#10;-A play consists of moving, shooting, and moving again (if possible).&#10;-It costs no movement points to turn and face any direction (0-5), and one movement point to enter an adjacent space&#10;-Different robots have different attributes as shown above&#10;-At the end of every turn, robots regenerate their movement points&#10;-Shooting at a space means selecting a range and direction causes the shooting-robot's attack-rating to be subtracted from the health of all robots in that space (friendly or enemy)&#10;-If a robot's health drops to zero or less than zero, the robot is dead and removed from play&#10;-Until a robot is dead, its movement and damage ratings are unimpaired&#10;-Note that range=0, direction=0 is invalid&#10;-If more than one team's robots are alive, another turn starts beginning with Red's highest-movement robot&#10;-If only one team's robots are alive, that team is the winner" wrapText="true">
